 BY AKINWALE ABOLUWADE A Grade’C’ Customary Court at Omoyeni Memorial Primary School, Ode-Aje, Ibadan has been gutted by fire. It was reported that the fire incident happened on Tuesday following an electrical spark. The roof of the building and other items were said to have been affected by the inferno. During a visit to the school on Wednesday, officials of the Oyo State Government promised to collaborate with relevant agencies to curb fire outbreak in public schools and other public utilities. The Executive Chairman, Oyo State Universal Basic Education Board, Dr. Nureni Adeniran, gave the assurance during an assessment of the Grade ‘C’ Customary Court building that was gutted by fire. Adeniran reiterated the Board’s commitment to the protection of schools in the state, especially during dry season. The education boss, who was accompanied by the Board and management team of the Agency, tasked head-teachers to ensure effective monitoring of classes and offices to guard against illicit connection of electrical appliances and acts capable of causing the fire. He charged them to be extra-vigilant and to report any activity that may pose a threat to schools. While sympathizing with the management of the Customary Court, on the incident, Adeniran lauded the school community for rallying round to put the fire under control. He said, “We commend you for being proactive and for your quick intervention which prevented this fire outbreak from spreading to classes here. “The Board is so grateful that there was no casualty and that this happened when pupils had left school. I enjoin you to ensure you monitor whatever these children are doing and make sure that all appliances are put off after school hours.” 